#: Game.Levels.SetOpsWorld.L13_DeMorgan
msgid "# De Morgan's Law for Sets\n"
"\n"
"One of the most important identities in set theory is **De Morgan's law**:\n"
"\n"
"¬ß0\n"
"\n"
"In words: the complement of a union equals the intersection of the\n"
"complements. An element is outside ¬ß1 if and only if it is\n"
"outside both ¬ß2 and ¬ß3.\n"
"\n"
"You already proved the ¬ß4 direction in Level 11 using ¬ß5.\n"
"Now you must prove the full **equality** ‚Äî both directions.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. ¬ß6 ‚Äî reduce to membership biconditional\n"
"2. ¬ß7 ‚Äî split the ¬ß8 into forward (¬ß9) and backward (¬ß10)\n"
"3. **Forward** (¬ß11): Given ¬ß12, prove ¬ß13.\n"
"   Use ¬ß14 and ¬ß15 as in Level 11.\n"
"4. **Backward** (¬ß16): Given ¬ß17, prove ¬ß18.\n"
"   Destructure the hypothesis, introduce the union assumption,\n"
"   then case-split.\n"
"\n"
"This is the longest proof in the world so far. Take it step by step ‚Äî\n"
"each individual step is familiar from earlier levels."
msgstr ""

