#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L10_ExtIntro
msgid "# Extensionality: When Two Sets Are Equal\n"
"\n"
"Two sets are equal when they have exactly the same elements:\n"
"\n"
"¬ß0\n"
"\n"
"This is the **Axiom of Extensionality** ‚Äî one of the foundational\n"
"axioms of set theory. It says that a set is nothing more than its\n"
"elements: two sets with the same members are the same set, regardless\n"
"of how they are described. The tactic ¬ß1\n"
"converts a set equality goal into: for each ¬ß2, prove the membership\n"
"biconditional ¬ß3.\n"
"\n"
"After ¬ß4, the goal becomes an ¬ß5. Use ¬ß6 to split it\n"
"into two implications (forward and backward), then prove each direction.\n"
"\n"
"After ¬ß7, you will see the ¬ß8 (focus dot) for the first time.\n"
"When Lean creates multiple subgoals, ¬ß9 **focuses** on one subgoal at\n"
"a time. Write ¬ß10 to apply ¬ß11 to the current subgoal only.\n"
"After that subgoal is closed, the next ¬ß12 picks up the next subgoal.\n"
"Think of ¬ß13 as \"now working on this case.\"\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that ¬ß14.\n"
"\n"
"The conjunction ¬ß15 is equivalent to just ¬ß16 because\n"
"¬ß17 already implies ¬ß18. So the second condition is redundant.\n"
"\n"
"This level is longer than previous ones ‚Äî the proof has several steps.\n"
"Do not worry: each step is guided by hints, and the math is simple.\n"
"The length comes from the proof structure, not from difficulty.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. ¬ß19 ‚Äî reduce to membership biconditional\n"
"2. ¬ß20 ‚Äî split the ¬ß21 into two directions\n"
"3. **Forward** (¬ß22): given ¬ß23, extract ¬ß24\n"
"4. **Backward** (¬ß25): given ¬ß26, build ¬ß27"
msgstr ""

