#: Game.Levels.SetWorld.L01_WelcomeToSets
msgid "# Welcome to Sets\n"
"\n"
"In Lean 4, a **set** is not a primitive concept ‚Äî it is built from\n"
"something you already know: **predicates**.\n"
"\n"
"The definition is:\n"
"¬ß0\n"
"\n"
"A set of natural numbers is just a function that takes a natural number\n"
"and returns a proposition. If the proposition is true, the number is\n"
"*in* the set; if false, it is *not* in the set.\n"
"\n"
"**Membership** ¬ß1 means: apply the predicate ¬ß2 to ¬ß3 and check\n"
"whether the result holds. So ¬ß4 is just ¬ß5 ‚Äî function application!\n"
"\n"
"The simplest set is ¬ß6, the **universal set**. Its predicate is\n"
"¬ß7 ‚Äî it returns ¬ß8 for every input. So ¬ß9\n"
"reduces to just ¬ß10.\n"
"\n"
"Look at your goal. The problem asks you to prove ¬ß11, but\n"
"the goal state shows ¬ß12 ‚Äî because Lean has already evaluated the\n"
"membership predicate for you. All you need to do is prove ¬ß13.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Use ¬ß14 to close the goal. (Recall that ¬ß15\n"
"is a type with exactly one constructor, ¬ß16, and ¬ß17\n"
"applies it.)"
msgstr ""

