#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L17_Boss
msgid "# Boss: Chaining Subsets to Prove Equality\n"
"\n"
"You have two sets ¬ß0 and ¬ß1 of natural numbers, with three\n"
"hypotheses:\n"
"- ¬ß2 ‚Äî ¬ß3 is contained in ¬ß4\n"
"- ¬ß5 ‚Äî ¬ß6 is contained in the numbers at most 4\n"
"- ¬ß7 ‚Äî every number less than 5 is in ¬ß8\n"
"\n"
"Your task: prove ¬ß9.\n"
"\n"
"Think about what this means. The hypothesis ¬ß10 tells you that\n"
"¬ß11. And from ¬ß12 and ¬ß13, you can chain:\n"
"¬ß14. Since ¬ß15 is the same as ¬ß16 for\n"
"natural numbers, this gives ¬ß17. Together with\n"
"¬ß18, you get equality by antisymmetry.\n"
