#: Game.Levels.SetWorld.L02_SetBuilder
msgid "# Set Builder Notation\n"
"\n"
"In mathematics, you write sets like ¬ß0.\n"
"In Lean, this becomes ¬ß1.\n"
"\n"
"This notation is syntactic sugar for ¬ß2, which is\n"
"defined as... just ¬ß3 itself! The function ¬ß4 is\n"
"literally the identity: it takes a predicate and returns it as a ¬ß5.\n"
"\n"
"So what happens when you check membership?\n"
