"using standard equivalences:\n"
"\n"
"| Before push_neg | After push_neg |\n"
"|---|---|\n"
"| ¬ß4 | ¬ß5 |\n"
"| ¬ß6 | ¬ß7 |\n"
"| ¬ß8 | ¬ß9 |\n"
"| ¬ß10 | ¬ß11 |\n"
"\n"
"You can apply it to a hypothesis with ¬ß12, or to the\n"
"goal with just ¬ß13.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that the complement of a union is contained in\n"
"the intersection of the complements. This is one direction of\n"
"**De Morgan's law** for sets:\n"
"\n"
"¬ß14\n"
"\n"
"After ¬ß15, you will have ¬ß16, which is\n"
"definitionally ¬ß17. Use ¬ß18 to make the negated\n"
"disjunction explicit, then ¬ß19 to convert it to\n"
"¬ß20 ‚Äî which matches the goal.\n"
"\n"
"**Why ¬ß21 is needed here**: Lean displays ¬ß22\n"
"using set-theoretic complement notation, but ¬ß23 needs to see\n"
"the negation explicitly as ¬ß24. The tactic\n"
"¬ß25 converts to this definitionally\n"
"equal logical form so ¬ß26 can process it. This\n"
"¬ß27 + ¬ß28 pattern will recur whenever you work with\n"
"complements of compound sets."
msgstr ""

