#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L07_NonSubset
msgid "# When ‚äÜ Fails: Proving ¬¨(s ‚äÜ t)\n"
"\n"
"All the subset proofs so far have been **positive**: you showed that\n"
"one set is contained in another. But what if the containment is\n"
"**false**? How do you prove ¬ß0?\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, ¬ß1 is defined as ¬ß2. So to prove ¬ß3,\n"
"you use ¬ß4 to **assume** the subset holds, getting\n"
"¬ß5, and then derive a contradiction (¬ß6).\n"
"\n"
"To derive the contradiction, exhibit a **counterexample**: find an\n"
"element that is in ¬ß7 but not in ¬ß8. If the subset held, this\n"
"element would have to be in both ‚Äî but it is not, so we get ¬ß9.\n"
"\n"
"In Level 1, we noted that ¬ß10 is false\n"
"because 4 is in the first set but not the second. Now you will prove\n"
"this formally.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. ¬ß11 ‚Äî assume the subset holds (goal becomes ¬ß12)\n"
"2. Prove ¬ß13 ‚Äî show the witness is in the domain\n"
"3. Apply ¬ß14 to get ¬ß15 ‚Äî use the assumed subset\n"
"4. Unwrap and derive contradiction ‚Äî ¬ß16 is false"
msgstr ""

